3. Key Challenges the Code Solves:
CRS (Coordinate Reference Systems): The most critical step. The report uses NAD83. In code, you must ensure every layer is reprojected (to_crs) to match, or the park will end up in the middle of the ocean.
Spatial Interpolation: The "gridded rainfall" doesnt usually come as a perfect image. It is often created from the station points using an algorithm like Kriging or IDW (Inverse Distance Weighting) to guess the values between the dots.
Alpha Blending: Note how you can see the mountains under the blue rainfall colors. In code, this is handled by the alpha parameter (transparency).
Legend Logic: Creating that custom legend requires manually mapping the color magenta square to "CDO Station" and orange circle to "HCDP Station."
Dynamic Alternatives
If you wanted this image to be interactive (where you could hover over a station point to see its name), you would use Folium (a Python wrapper for Leaflet.js). This allows you to toggle the layers on and off just like a modern digital map.